er.md\\n\\n**Step 3 (line 38)** lists 11 `Agent` interface methods but the actual interface has 15. Missing:\\n- `GetSessionID(input *HookInput) string`\\n- `ReadSession(input *HookInput) (*AgentSession, error)`\\n- `WriteSession(ctx context.Context, session *AgentSession) error`\\n- `FormatResumeCommand(sessionID string) string`\\n\\n**Step 5 (line 91) and line 105** use wrong `TranscriptAnalyzer` method names:\\n| implementer.md says | Actual method in agent.go |\\n|---|---|\\n| `ExtractFilesTouched` | `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` |\\n| `ExtractUserPrompts` | `ExtractPrompts` |\\n| `GenerateContext` | `ExtractSummary` |\\n| *(missing)* | `GetTranscriptPosition` |\\n\\n### Finding 2: CONFIRMED HIGH ã Mixed hook/event names in implementer.md\\n\\nLines 65, 79, 88 use Claude Code-specific native hook names where EventType names should be used:\\n| implementer.md says | Should say (EventType) |\\n|---|---|\\n| `Stop` (lines 65, 79, 88) | `TurnEnd` (or `SessionEnd`) |\\n| `UserPromptSubmit` (line 88) | `TurnStart` |\\n| `SubagentTaskStart`/`SubagentTaskEnd` (line 88) | `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd` |\\n\\nThese are agent-specific hook verbs, not normalized EventType values. An implementer following these literally for a non-Claude agent would assert on wrong types.\\n\\n### Finding 3: CONFIRMED MEDIUM ã AGENT_SLUG ambiguity\\n\\nReal-world evidence from Gemini:\\n- Go package dir: `geminicli/` (no hyphen ã Go requires this)\\n- Agent registry key (AgentName): `\\\"gemini\\\"`\\n- E2E Name(): `\\\"gemini-cli\\\"`\\n- E2E_AGENT filter: `\\\"gemini-cli\\\"`\\n\\nA single `AGENT_SLUG` can't serve all four roles. If set to `\\\"gemini\\\"`, the E2E filter is wrong. If set to `\\\"gemini-cli\\\"`, it's an invalid Go package name.\\n\\n### Finding 4: CONFIRMED MEDIUM ã Hook-only scope not declared\\n\\nimplementer.md Step 3 (line 41) mandates `hooks.go` with `InstallHooks`/`UninstallHooks`/`AreHooksInstalled`. Step 4 starts with hook-exercising tests. But `agent.go:111` defines `FileWatcher` as an alternative integration path. The skill doesn't mention FileWatcher or scope itself to hook-capable agents.\\n\\n### Finding 5: CONFIRMED LOW ã Checklist reference conflict\\n\\nSKILL.md:31 lists `agent-integration-checklist.md` in Architecture References. researcher.md:11 says \\\"Do NOT read ... checklist.\\\" Mild confusion for the researcher phase.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Design Principle: Reference Source, Don't Hardcode\\n\\nThe root cause of findings 1-3 is hardcoded names that drift from the source code. The fix pattern is:\\n- **Never list method names** ã say \\\"all methods from the `Agent` interface in `agent.go`\\\"\\n- **Never list EventType values** ã say \\\"use `EventType` constants from `event.go`\\\"\\n- **Point to existing agents** as examples of naming patterns rather than encoding naming rules\\n\\nThis means the skill files age gracefully ã when interfaces change, the implementer reads the current source.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Fixes\\n\\n### Fix 1: Remove hardcoded method lists from implementer.md (Findings 1 & 2)\\n\\n**File:** `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`\\n\\n**Step 3 (line 38)** ã Replace the parenthetical method list with a source reference:\\n\\n```\\n- (Name, Type, Description, IsPreview, DetectPresence, ProtectedDirs, GetSessionDir, ResolveSessionFile, ReadTranscript, ChunkTranscript, ReassembleTranscript).\\n+ (every method in the `Agent` interface ã refer to `agent.go` from Step 1). Include `HookSupport` methods in `lifecycle.go` and `hooks.go`.\\n```\\n\\n**Step 5 line 91** ã Replace hardcoded TranscriptAnalyzer method names:\\n\\n```\\n- `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods: `ExtractFilesTouched`, `ExtractUserPrompts`, `GenerateContext`\\n+ `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods (see `agent.go` for current method signatures)\\n```\\n\\n**Step 5 line 105** ã Same for test targets:\\n\\n```\\n- Test `ExtractFilesTouched`, `ExtractUserPrompts`, `GenerateContext` if `TranscriptAnalyzer` is implemented.\\n+ Test all `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods (from `agent.go`) if implemented.\\n```\\n\\n### Fix 2: Replace native hook names with source-referencing language (Finding 2)\\n\\n**File:** `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`\\n\\nThe issue: Steps 4-5 use Claude Code-specific hook verbs (`Stop`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `SubagentTaskStart`) where they mean normalized EventTypes (`TurnEnd`, `TurnStart`, `SubagentStart`). Instead of replacing one set of hardcoded names with another, reference the source.\\n\\n**Step 4 line 65** ã Replace:\\n```\\n- `ParseHookEvent()` ã at minimum, the `SessionStart` and `Stop` event types\\n+ `ParseHookEvent()` ã at minimum, the event types needed for session start and turn end (see `EventType` constants in `event.go`)\\n```\\n\\n**Step 4 line 79** ã Replace:\\n```\\n- Test `ParseHookEvent` for the event types exercised so far (`SessionStart`, `Stop`). Include nil return for unknown hook names and malformed JSON input.\\n+ Test `ParseHookEvent` for the event types exercised so far. Include nil return for unknown hook names and malformed JSON input. **Important:** Test against `EventType` constants from `event.go`, not native hook names ã the agent's native hook verbs (e.g., \\\"stop\\\") map to normalized EventTypes (e.g., `TurnEnd`).\\n```\\n\\n**Step 5 line 88** ã Replace:\\n```\\n- Complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all 4 basic events: `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `SubagentTaskStart`/`SubagentTaskEnd` (if applicable), `Stop`\\n+ Complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all lifecycle event types from `event.go`. Use the one-pager's hook mapping table to translate native hook names to `EventType` constants.\\n```\\n\\n### Fix 3: Split AGENT_SLUG into distinct parameters (Finding 3)\\n\\n**File:** `.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md`\\n\\nReplace the current parameter table with parameters that match real-world naming splits. Instead of hardcoded examples, reference existing agents:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Parameter | Description | How to derive |\\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\\n| `AGENT_NAME` | Human-readable name (e.g., \\\"Gemini CLI\\\") | User provides |\\n| `AGENT_PACKAGE` | Go package dir name ã **no hyphens** | Lowercase, remove hyphens/spaces |\\n| `AGENT_KEY` | Registry key for `agent.Register()` and `entire enable` | Check existing patterns in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` |\\n| `AGENT_BIN` | CLI binary name | `command -v <binary>` |\\n| `LIVE_COMMAND` | Full command to launch agent | User provides |\\n| `EVENTS_OR_UNKNOWN` | Known hook event names, or \\\"unknown\\\" | From agent docs or \\\"unknown\\\" |\\n\\n**Note:** These identifiers can differ. Run `grep -r 'AgentName\\\\|func.*Name()' cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/` and `e2e/agents/` to see how existing agents handle the split.\\n```\\n\\nThen update references across all four skill files:\\n- `$AGENT_SLUG` in Go directory paths ã `$AGENT_PACKAGE`\\n- `$AGENT_SLUG` in `agent.Register(...)` ã `$AGENT_KEY`\\n- `$AGENT_SLUG` in E2E, scripts, probe dirs ã keep as `$AGENT_SLUG` (derived from `$AGENT_KEY` or user preference)\\n\\nSince most references are directory paths, the bulk rename is `AGENT_SLUG` ã `AGENT_PACKAGE` for Go paths, with `AGENT_KEY` only where the registry key is needed.\\n\\n### Fix 4: Add hook-only scope note to SKILL.md (Finding 4)\\n\\n**File:** `.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md`\\n\\nAdd before the Pipeline section:\\n\\n```markdown\\n## Scope\\n\\nThis skill targets **hook-capable agents** ã those that support lifecycle hooks\\n(implementing `HookSupport` from `agent.go`). Agents that use file-based detection\\n(implementing `FileWatcher`) require a different integration approach not covered here.\\nCheck `agent.go` for the current interface definitions.\\n```\\n\\nReferences the interface names from source rather than listing agent examples.\\n\\n### Fix 5: Remove checklist from researcher's \\\"do not read\\\" list (Finding 5)\\n\\n**File:** `.claude