t passes\\n    75ã\\n    76ã**After passing, write unit tests:**\\n    77ã\\n    78ã- `hooks_test.go` ã Test `InstallHooks` (creates config, idempotent), `UninstallHooks` (removes hooks), `AreHooksInstalled` (detects presence). Use a temp directory to avoid touching real config.\\n    79ã- `lifecycle_test.go` (initial) ã Test `ParseHookEvent` for the event types exercised so far (`SessionStart`, `Stop`). Include nil return for unknown hook names and malformed JSON input.\\n    80ã\\n    81ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n    82ã\\n    83ã### Step 5: E2E Tier 2 ã `TestSingleSessionManualCommit`\\n    84ã\\n    85ãThe foundational test. This exercises the full agent lifecycle: start session ã agent prompt ã agent produces files ã user commits ã session ends.\\n    86ã\\n    87ã**What it exercises:**\\n    88ã- Complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all 4 basic events: `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `SubagentTaskStart`/`SubagentTaskEnd` (if applicable), `Stop`\\n    89ã- `GetSessionDir` / `ResolveSessionFile` ã finding the agent's session/transcript files\\n    90ã- `ReadTranscript` / `ChunkTranscript` / `ReassembleTranscript` ã reading native transcript format\\n    91ã- `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods: `ExtractFilesTouched`, `ExtractUserPrompts`, `GenerateContext`\\n    92ã\\n    93ã**Cycle:**\\n    94ã\\n    95ã1. Run: `mise run test:e2e:$AGENT_SLUG TestSingleSessionManualCommit`\\n    96ã2. Read the failure output carefully\\n    97ã3. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to understand what happened\\n    98ã4. Implement the minimum code to fix the first failure\\n    99ã5. Repeat until the test passes\\n   100ã\\n   101ã**After passing, write unit tests:**\\n   102ã\\n   103ã- `types_test.go` ã Test hook input struct parsing with actual JSON payloads from `AGENT.md` examples or captured payloads.\\n   104ã- `lifecycle_test.go` (complete) ã Test `ParseHookEvent` for all 4 event types. Use actual JSON payloads. Test every `EventType` mapping, nil returns for pass-through hooks, empty input, and malformed JSON.\\n   105ã- `transcript_test.go` ã Test `ReadTranscript`, `ChunkTranscript`, `ReassembleTranscript` with sample data in the agent's native format. Test `ExtractFilesTouched`, `ExtractUserPrompts`, `GenerateContext` if `TranscriptAnalyzer` is implemented.\\n   106ã\\n   107ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   108ã\\n   109ã### Step 6: E2E Tier 2b ã `TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation`\\n   110ã\\n   111ãValidates transcript quality: JSONL validity, content hash correctness, prompt extraction accuracy.\\n   112ã\\n   113ã**What it exercises:**\\n   114ã- Transcript content stored at checkpoints is valid JSONL\\n   115ã- Content hash matches the stored transcript\\n   116ã- User prompts are correctly extracted\\n   117ã- Metadata fields are populated\\n   118ã\\n   119ã**Cycle:**\\n   120ã\\n   121ã1. Run: `mise run test:e2e:$AGENT_SLUG TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation`\\n   122ã2. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on any failures ã this test often exposes subtle transcript formatting bugs\\n   123ã3. Fix and repeat\\n   124ã\\n   125ã**After passing:** Update `transcript_test.go` if any edge cases were discovered.\\n   126ã\\n   127ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   128ã\\n   129ã### Step 7: E2E Tier 3 ã `TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn`\\n   130ã\\n   131ãAgent creates files and commits them within a single prompt turn. Tests the in-turn commit path.\\n   132ã\\n   133ã**What it exercises:**\\n   134ã- Hook events firing during an agent's commit (post-commit hooks while agent is active)\\n   135ã- Checkpoint creation when agent commits mid-turn\\n   136ã- Usually no new agent-specific code needed ã this tests the strategy's handling of agent commits\\n   137ã\\n   138ã**Cycle:**\\n   139ã\\n   140ã1. Run: `mise run test:e2e:$AGENT_SLUG TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn`\\n   141ã2. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on failures\\n   142ã3. Fix and repeat ã if the agent doesn't support committing, skip this test\\n   143ã\\n   144ã**After passing:** Add any new edge cases to existing unit tests if bugs were found.\\n   145ã\\n   146ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   147ã\\n   148ã### Step 8: E2E Tier 4 ã Multi-Session Tests\\n   149ã\\n   150ãRun these tests to validate multi-session behavior:\\n   151ã\\n   152ã- `TestMultiSessionManualCommit` ã Two sessions, both produce files, user commits\\n   153ã- `TestMultiSessionSequential` ã Sessions run one after another\\n   154ã- `TestEndedSessionUserCommitsAfterExit` ã User commits after session ends\\n   155ã\\n   156ã**Cycle (for each test):**\\n   157ã\\n   158ã1. Run: `mise run test:e2e:$AGENT_SLUG TestMultiSessionManualCommit`\\n   159ã2. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on failures\\n   160ã3. Fix and repeat\\n   161ã4. Move to next test\\n   162ã\\n   163ã**After all pass:** These tests rarely need new agent code ã they exercise the strategy layer. Update unit tests only if agent-specific bugs were found.\\n   164ã\\n   165ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   166ã\\n   167ã### Step 9: E2E Tier 5 ã File Operation Edge Cases\\n   168ã\\n   169ãRun these tests for file operation correctness:\\n   170ã\\n   171ã- `TestModifyExistingTrackedFile` ã Agent modifies (not creates) a file\\n   172ã- `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges` ã User stages only some of the agent's changes\\n   173ã- `TestDeletedFilesCommitDeletion` ã Agent deletes a file, user commits the deletion\\n   174ã- `TestMixedNewAndModifiedFiles` ã Agent both creates and modifies files\\n   175ã\\n   176ã**Cycle:** Same as above ã run each test, use `/debug-e2e` on failures, fix, repeat.\\n   177ã\\n   178ã**After all pass:** Update unit tests if any transcript parsing or file-touched extraction bugs were discovered.\\n   179ã\\n   180ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   181ã\\n   182ã### Step 10: Optional Interfaces\\n   183ã\\n   184ãRead `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` for all optional interfaces. For each one the one-pager's \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" or \\\"Transcript\\\" sections suggest is feasible:\\n   185ã\\n   186ã- **`TranscriptPreparer`** ã If the agent needs pre-processing before transcript storage\\n   187ã- **`TokenCalculator`** ã If the agent provides token usage data\\n   188ã- **`SubagentAwareExtractor`** ã If the agent has subagent/tool-use patterns\\n   189ã\\n   190ãFor each optional interface:\\n   191ã\\n   192ã1. Implement the methods based on `AGENT.md` and reference implementation\\n   193ã2. Write unit tests for the new methods\\n   194ã3. Run relevant E2E tests to verify integration\\n   195ã\\n   196ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   197ã\\n   198ã### Step 11: E2E Tier 6 ã Interactive and Rewind Tests\\n   199ã\\n   200ãRun these if the agent supports interactive multi-step sessions:\\n   201ã\\n   202ã- `TestInteractiveMultiStep` ã Multiple prompts in one session\\n   203ã- `TestRewindPreCommit` ã Rewind to a checkpoint before committing\\n   204ã- `TestRewindAfterCommit` ã Rewind to a checkpoint after committing\\n   205ã- `TestRewindMultipleFiles` ã Rewind with multiple files changed\\n   206ã\\n   207ã**Cycle:** Same pattern ã run, `/debug-e2e` on failures, fix, repeat.\\n   208ã\\n   209ãRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   210ã\\n   211ã### Step 12: E2E Tier 7 ã Complex Scenarios\\n   212ã\\n   213ãRun the remaining edge case and stress tests:\\n   214ã\\n   215ã- `TestPartialCommitStashNewPrompt` ã Partial commit, stash, new prompt\\n   216ã- `TestStashSecondPromptUnstas