est-writer and implementer phases will use as their single source of agent-specific information.\\n    71ã\\n    72ã**Create the agent package directory first** (if it doesn't exist):\\n    73ã\\n    74ã```bash\\n    75ãmkdir -p cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG\\n    76ã```\\n    77ã\\n    78ã**Write the one-pager using this template:**\\n    79ã\\n    80ã```markdown\\n    81ã# $AGENT_NAME ã Integration One-Pager\\n    82ã\\n    83ã## Verdict: COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n    84ã\\n    85ã## Static Checks\\n    86ã| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    87ã|-------|--------|-------|\\n    88ã| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    89ã| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n    90ã| Version info | PASS/FAIL | version string |\\n    91ã| Hook keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    92ã| Session keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    93ã| Config directory | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    94ã| Documentation | PASS/FAIL | URL |\\n    95ã\\n    96ã## Binary\\n    97ã- Name: `$AGENT_BIN`\\n    98ã- Version: ...\\n    99ã- Install: ... (how to install if not present)\\n   100ã\\n   101ã## Hook Mechanism\\n   102ã- Config file: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json` (exact path)\\n   103ã- Config format: JSON / YAML / TOML\\n   104ã- Hook registration: ... (how hooks are declared ã JSON objects, env vars, etc.)\\n   105ã- Hook names and when they fire:\\n   106ã  | Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Entire EventType |\\n   107ã  |-----------------|---------------|-----------------|\\n   108ã  | `on_session_start` | Agent session begins | `SessionStart` |\\n   109ã  | ... | ... | ... |\\n   110ã- Valid Entire EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n   111ã- Hook input (stdin JSON): ... (exact fields with example payload)\\n   112ã\\n   113ã## Transcript\\n   114ã- Location: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/sessions/<