 for interactive PTY-based tests: `NewTmuxSession`, `Send`, `SendKeys`, `WaitFor` (with settle-time logic), `Capture`, `Close`\\n    22ã5. `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` ã Rich assertion helpers: `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForFileExists`, `AssertNewCommits`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointAdvanced`, `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer`, `AssertCheckpointExists`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, and many more\\n    23ã6. `e2e/testutil/metadata.go` ã `CheckpointMetadata`, `SessionMetadata`, `TokenUsage`, `Attribution`, `SessionRef` types; `CheckpointPath()` helper for sharded directory layout\\n    24ã7. `e2e/entire/entire.go` ã CLI wrapper: `BinPath()` (builds from source or uses `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN`), `Enable`, `Disable`, `RewindList`, `Rewind`, `RewindLogsOnly`, `Explain`, `ExplainGenerate`, `ExplainCommit`, `Resume`\\n    25ã8. `e2e/testutil/artifacts.go` ã Automatic artifact capture via `t.Cleanup`: `CaptureArtifacts` saves git-log, git-tree, checkpoint metadata, entire logs, and tmux pane content\\n    26ã\\n    27ã### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Test Scenarios\\n    28ã\\n    29ãRun `Glob(\\\"e2e/tests/*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing test files. Read a few to understand the patterns:\\n    30ã- How tests use `testutil.ForEachAgent` with a timeout and callback `func(t, s, ctx)`\\n    31ã- How prompts are written inline (no separate prompt template file)\\n    32ã- How `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.StartSession`, `s.WaitFor`, `s.Send` are used\\n    33ã- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, metadata, etc.\\n    34ã\\n    35ã### Step 3: Read Checkpoint Scenarios Doc\\n    36ã\\n    37ãRead `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` for the state machine and scenarios the tests should cover.\\n    38ã\\n    39ã### Step 4: Create Agent Implementation\\n    40ã\\n    41ãRead `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` (the one-pager from the research phase) for all agent-specific information:\\n    42ã- Binary name ã \\\"Binary\\\" section\\n    43ã- Prompt flags ã \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    44ã- Interactive mode ã \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    45ã- Transient error patterns ã \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" section (use defaults if not listed)\\n    46ã- Bootstrap setup ã \\\"Config Preservation\\\" section\\n    47ã\\n    48ã**If something is missing from the one-pager**, you may search external docs ã but update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover.\\n    49ã\\n    50ãAdd a new `Agent` implementation in `e2e/agents/${agent_slug}.go`:\\n    51ã\\n    52ã**Pattern to follow** (based on existing implementations like `claude.go`, `gemini.go`, `opencode.go`):\\n    53ã\\n    54ã```go\\n    55ãpackage agents\\n    56ã\\n    57ãimport (\\n    58ã\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n    59ã\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n    60ã\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n    61ã\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    62ã\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    63ã\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    64ã\\t\\\"syscall\\\"\\n    65ã\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    66ã)\\n    67ã\\n    68ãfunc init() {\\n    69ã\\tif env := os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_AGENT\\\"); env != \\\"\\\" && env != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n    70ã\\t\\treturn\\n    71ã\\t}\\n    72ã\\tRegister(&${AgentName}{})\\n    73ã\\t// Optional: limit concurrency for rate-limited agents\\n    74ã\\t// RegisterGate(\\\"${agent-slug}\\\", 1)\\n    75ã}\\n    76ã\\n    77ãtype ${AgentName} struct{}\\n    78ã\\n    79ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) Name() string               { return \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" }\\n    80ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) Binary() string             { return \\\"${binary-name}\\\" }\\n    81ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) EntireAgent() string        { return \\\"${entire-agent-name}\\\" }\\n    82ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) PromptPattern() string      { return `${prompt-regex}` }\\n    83ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) TimeoutMultiplier() float64 { return 1.0 }\\n    84ã\\n    85ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) Bootstrap() error {\\n    86ã\\t// CI-specific setup: auth config, API key injection, warmup, etc.\\n    87ã\\t// Must be idempotent. Called once before any tests run.\\n    88ã\\treturn nil\\n    89ã}\\n    90ã\\n    91ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) IsTransientError(out Output, err error) bool {\\n    92ã\\tif err == nil {\\n    93ã\\t\\treturn false\\n    94ã\\t}\\n    95ã\\tcombined := out.Stdout + out.Stderr\\n    96ã\\tfor _, p := range []string{\\\"overloaded\\\", \\\"rate limit\\\", \\\"503\\\", \\\"529\\\"} {\\n    97ã\\t\\tif strings.Contains(combined, p) {\\n    98ã\\t\\t\\treturn true\\n    99ã\\t\\t}\\n   100ã\\t}\\n   101ã\\treturn false\\n   102ã}\\n   103ã\\n   104ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n   105ã\\tcfg := &runConfig{}\\n   106ã\\tfor _, o := range opts {\\n   107ã\\t\\to(cfg)\\n   108ã\\t}\\n   109ã\\n   110ã\\targs := []string{/* agent CLI flags for non-interactive prompt execution */}\\n   111ã\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, a.Binary(), args...)\\n   112ã\\tcmd.Dir = dir\\n   113ã\\tcmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\")\\n   114ã\\tcmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{Setpgid: true}\\n   115ã\\tcmd.Cancel = func() error {\\n   116ã\\t\\treturn syscall.Kill(-cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGKILL)\\n   117ã\\t}\\n   118ã\\n   119ã\\tvar stdout, stderr strings.Builder\\n   120ã\\tcmd.Stdout = &stdout\\n   121ã\\tcmd.Stderr = &stderr\\n   122ã\\n   123ã\\terr := cmd.Run()\\n   124ã\\texitCode := 0\\n   125ã\\tif err != nil {\\n   126ã\\t\\texitErr := &exec.ExitError{}\\n   127ã\\t\\tif errors.As(err, &exitErr) {\\n   128ã\\t\\t\\texitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\\n   129ã\\t\\t} else {\\n   130ã\\t\\t\\texitCode = -1\\n   131ã\\t\\t}\\n   132ã\\t}\\n   133ã\\n   134ã\\treturn Output{\\n   135ã\\t\\tCommand:  a.Binary() + \\\" \\\" + strings.Join(args, \\\" \\\"),\\n   136ã\\t\\tStdout:   stdout.String(),\\n   137ã\\t\\tStderr:   stderr.String(),\\n   138ã\\t\\tExitCode: exitCode,\\n   139ã\\t}, err\\n   140ã}\\n   141ã\\n   142ãfunc (a *${AgentName}) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n   143ã\\t// Use NewTmuxSession for interactive PTY support.\\n   144ã\\t// Return nil if agent doesn't support interactive mode.\\n   145ã\\tname := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"${agent-slug}-test-%d\\\", time.Now().UnixNano())\\n   146ã\\ts, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, nil, a.Binary(), /* interactive args */)\\n   147ã\\tif err != nil {\\n   148ã\\t\\treturn nil, err\\n   149ã\\t}\\n   150ã\\treturn s, nil\\n   151ã}\\n   152ã```\\n   153ã\\n   154ãKey implementation details:\\n   155ã- Self-register in `init()` with `Register()`, gated by `E2E_AGENT` env var\\n   156ã- Use `RegisterGate(\\\"name\\\", N)` if the agent's API has strict rate limits (e.g., Gemini uses gate of 1)\\n   157ã- `Bootstrap()` handles CI-specific one-time setup (auth config, API key injection)\\n   158ã- `IsTransientError()` identifies retryable API failures ã `RepoState.RunPrompt` retries once on transient errors\\n   159ã- `RunPrompt()` uses `exec.CommandContext` with `Setpgid: true` and process-group kill for clean cancellation\\n   160ã- `StartSession()` uses `NewTmuxSession` for interactive PTY tests; return `nil` if interactive mode isn't supported\\n   161ã- Use `AGENT.md` (the one-pager) for CLI flags, prompt passing mechanism, and env vars\\n   162ã\\n   163ã### Step 5: Update SetupRepo (if needed)\\n   164ã\\n   165ãCheck if `testutil.SetupRepo` in `e2e/testutil/repo.go` needs agent-specific configuration. Look for the existing `if agent.Name() == \\\"opencode\\\"` block as an example:\\n   166ã\\n   167ã- Agent-specific config files that must exist before `entire enable`\\n   168ã- Permission or auth config files\\n   169ã- Environment variables needed for hook testing\\n   170ã\\n   171ãIf no special setup is needed, skip this step.\\n   172ã\\n   173ã### Step 6: Write E2E Test Scenarios\\n   174ã\\n   175ãExisting tests are agent-agnostic (they use `ForEachAgent`), so they should already work with the new agent. **Only create new test files if the agent has unique behaviors** that existing scenarios don't cover.\\n   176ã\\n   177ãCheck if all existing scenarios work by reviewing:\\n   178ã- Does the agent support non-interactive prompt mode? (required for `RunPrompt`)\\n   179ã- Does the agent create files when prompted? (required for basic workflow)\\n   180ã- Does the agent support git operations? (required for commit scenarios)\\n   181ã- Does the agent support interactive mode? (required for interactive tests ã can return nil from `StartSession`)\\n   182ã\\n   183ãIf the agent has unique behaviors, create new test files in `e2e/tests/`:\\n   184ã\\n   185ã```go\\n   186ã//go:build e2e\\n   187ã\\n   188ãpackage tests\\n   189ã\\n   190ãimport (\\n   191ã\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n   192ã\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n   193ã\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n   194ã\\n   195ã\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/e2e/testutil\\\"\\n   196ã)\\n   197ã\\n   198ãfunc TestAgentSpecificBehavior(t *testing.T) {\\n   199ã\\ttestutil.ForEachAgent(t, 2*time.Minute, func(t *testing.T, s *testutil.RepoState, ctx context.Context) {\\n   200ã\\t\\t// Skip for agents that don't apply\\n   201ã\\t\\tif s.Agent.Name() != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n   202ã\\t\\t\\tt.Skip(\\\"only applies to ${agent-slug}\\\")\\n   203ã\\t\\t}\\n   204ã\\n   205ã\\t\\t// Use s.RunPrompt for non-interactive, s.StartSession for interactive\\n   206ã\\t\\t_, err := s.RunPrompt(t, ctx,\\n   207ã\\t\\t\\t\\\"create a file at hello.txt with 'hello world'. Do not ask for confirmation.\\\")\\n   208ã\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   209ã\\t\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"agent failed: %v\\\", err)\\n   210ã\\t\\t}\\n   211ã\\n   212ã\\t\\ttestutil.AssertFileExists(t, s.Dir, \\\"hello.txt\\\")\\n   213ã\\t})\\n   214ã}\\n   215ã```\\n   216ã\\n   217ãSee `e2e/README.md` for the canonical reference on structure, debugging, and CI workflows.\\n   218ã\\n   219ã### Step 7: Verify\\n   220ã\\n   221ãAfter writing the code:\\n   222ã\\n   223ã1. **Lint check**: `mise run lint` ã ensure no lint errors\\n   224ã2. **Compile check**: `go test -c -tags=e2e ./e2e/tests` ã compile-only with the build tag to verify the code compiles\\n   225ã3. **List what to run**: Print the exact E2E commands but do NOT run them (they cost money):\\n   226ã   ```bash\\n   227ã   mise run test:e2e:${agent_slug} TestSingleSessionManualCommit\\n   228ã   ```\\n   229ã4. **Debug failures**: If tests fail, use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to diagnose ã artifacts are auto-captured to `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/`\\n   230ã5. **Add mise task**: Remind the user to add a `test:e2e:${agent_slug}` task in `mise.toml` and update CI workflows\\n   231ã\\n   232ã## Key Conventions\\n   233ã\\n   234ã- **Build tag**: All E2E test files must have `//go:build e2e` as the first line\\n   235ã- **Package**: `package tests` for test files in `e2e/tests/`; `package agents` for agent implementations in `e2e/agents/`\\n   236ã- **Parallel**: `ForEachAgent` handles parallelism ã do not call `t.Parallel()` inside the callback\\n   237ã- **Repo setup**: `ForEachAgent` calls `SetupRepo` automatically ã do not call it manually\\n   238ã- **Prompts**: Write prompts inline in the test. Include \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prevent agent stalling\\n   239ã- **Assertions**: Use helpers from `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` ã see `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, etc.\\n   240ã- **CLI operations**: Use the `e2e/entire` package (`entire.Enable`, `entire.RewindList`, `entire.Rewind`, etc.) ã never call