se run test`\\n\\n### Step 11: E2E Tier 6 ã Interactive and Rewind Tests\\n\\nRun these if the agent supports interactive multi-step sessions:\\n\\n- `TestInteractiveMultiStep` ã Multiple prompts in one session\\n- `TestRewindPreCommit` ã Rewind to a checkpoint before committing\\n- `TestRewindAfterCommit` ã Rewind to a checkpoint after committing\\n- `TestRewindMultipleFiles` ã Rewind with multiple files changed\\n\\n**Cycle:** Same pattern ã run, `/debug-e2e` on failures, fix, repeat.\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n\\n### Step 12: E2E Tier 7 ã Complex Scenarios\\n\\nRun the remaining edge case and stress tests:\\n\\n- `TestPartialCommitStashNewPrompt` ã Partial commit, stash, new prompt\\n- `TestStashSecondPromptUnstashCommitAll` ã Stash workflow across prompts\\n- `TestRapidSequentialCommits` ã Multiple commits in quick succession\\n- `TestAgentContinuesAfterCommit` ã Agent keeps working after a commit\\n- `TestSubagentCommitFlow` ã If the agent has subagent support\\n- `TestSingleSessionSubagentCommitInTurn` ã Subagent commits during a turn\\n\\n**Cycle:** Same pattern. Many of these require no new agent code ã they exercise strategy-layer behavior.\\n\\nRun: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n\\n### Step 13: Verify Registration\\n\\nVerify that registration from Step 3 is correct and complete:\\n\\n1. The `init()` function in `${AGENT_SLUG}.go` calls `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_SLUG\\\"), New)`\\n2. The blank import in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` is present\\n3. Run the full test suite: `mise run test:ci`\\n\\n### Step 14: Final Validation\\n\\nRun the complete validation:\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt      # Format\\nmise run lint     # Lint\\nmise run test:ci  # All tests (unit + integration)\\n```\\n\\nCheck against the integration checklist (`docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`):\\n\\n- [ ] Full transcript stored at every checkpoint\\n- [ ] Native format preserved\\n- [ ] All mappable hook events implemented\\n- [ ] Session storage working\\n- [ ] Hook installation/uninstallation working\\n- [ ] Tests pass with `t.Parallel()`\\n\\n## E2E Debugging Protocol\\n\\nAt every E2E failure, follow this protocol:\\n\\n1. **Read the test output** ã the assertion message often tells you exactly what's wrong\\n2. **Find the artifact directory** ã E2E tests save artifacts (logs, transcripts, git state) to a temp dir printed in the output\\n3. **Run `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}`** ã this skill analyzes artifacts and diagnoses the root cause\\n4. **Implement the minimum fix** ã don't over-engineer; fix only what the test demands\\n5. **Re-run the failing test** ã not the whole suite, just the one test\\n\\n## Key Patterns to Follow\\n\\n- **Use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]`** for parsing hook stdin JSON\\n- **Use `paths.WorktreeRoot()`** not `os.Getwd()` for git-relative paths\\n- **Preserve unknown config keys** when modifying agent config files (don't clobber user settings)\\n- **Use `logging.Debug/Info/Warn/Error`** for internal logging, not `fmt.Print`\\n- **Keep interface implementations minimal** ã only implement what's needed\\n- **Follow Go idioms** from `.golangci.yml` ã check before writing code\\n\\n## Output\\n\\nSummarize what was implemented:\\n- Package directory and files created\\n- Interfaces implemented (core + optional)\\n- Hook names registered\\n- Test coverage (number of test functions, what they cover)\\n- Any gaps or TODOs remaining\\n- E2E tests passing (list which ones pass)\\n- Commands to run full validation\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":4,\"oldLines\":7,\"newStart\":4,\"newLines\":7,\"lines\":[\" \",\" ## Prerequisites\",\" \",\"-- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md`\",\"+- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md`\",\" - The E2E test runner already added (from `write-tests` command)\",\" - If 